  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the sampling technique described as <em>Simple Random Sample</em>, <em>Stratified Random Sampling</em>, <em>Cluster Sampling</em> or <em>Multi-Stage Sampling</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>To measure the support for the current mayor in comparison to income, random constituents within a city are surveyed.</li>
              <li>To measure student satisfaction, classes are randomly selected and the students in those classes are surveyed.</li>
              <li>To measure student response to a new general education policy, the administration randomly selects students from the university to survey.</li>
              <li>To test the effects of a new fertilizer on apples, a farmer randomly selects a number of trees trees   and randomly selects a few apples from those trees to test.</li>
              <li>To test products for defects, a manufacturer randomly selects hours of the week and randomly tests products produced in those hours.</li>
              <li>To test products for defects, a manufacturer randomly selects hours of the week and tests all products produced in those hours.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
